item.title: CVE-2017-14587|2024-09-17T01:55:33.174Z -- atlassian -- atlassian%20fisheye%20and%20crucible
item.description: The administration user deletion resource in Atlassian Fisheye and Crucible before version 4.4.2 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary HTML or JavaScript via a cross site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in the uname parameter.

item.title: CVE-2017-14588|2024-09-17T00:56:07.229Z -- atlassian -- atlassian%20fisheye%20and%20crucible
item.description: Various resources in Atlassian Fisheye and Crucible before version 4.4.2 allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary HTML or JavaScript via a cross site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in the dialog parameter.

item.title: CVE-2017-9508|2024-09-17T03:23:29.429Z -- atlassian -- atlassian%20fisheye%20and%20crucible
item.description: Various resources in Atlassian Fisheye and Crucible before version 4.4.1 allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary HTML or JavaScript via a cross site scripting (XSS) vulnerability through the name of a repository or review file.
